      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Here's what I found about the paper **\"Language Modeling Is Compression\"**:\n\n## Paper Overview\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The paper is authored by Grégoire Delétang, Anian Ruoss, Paul-Ambroise Duquenne, Elliot Catt, Tim Genewein, Christopher Mattern, Jordi Grau-Moya, Li Kevin Wenliang, Matthew Aitchison, Laurent Orseau, Marcus Hutter, and Joel Veness."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "It was published at ICLR 2024."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n**Key Idea:** "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "It has long been established that predictive models can be transformed into lossless compressors and vice versa. In recent years, the machine learning community has focused on training increasingly large and powerful self-supervised (language) models. Since these large language models exhibit impressive predictive capabilities, they are well-positioned to be strong compressors. The authors advocate for viewing the prediction problem through the lens of compression and evaluate the compression capabilities of large (foundation) models."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n**Main Findings:**\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The authors show that large language models are powerful general-purpose predictors and that the compression viewpoint provides novel insights into scaling laws, tokenization, and in-context learning."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "For example, Chinchilla 70B, while trained primarily on text, compresses ImageNet patches to 43.4% and LibriSpeech samples to 16.4% of their raw size, beating domain-specific compressors like PNG (58.5%) or FLAC (30.3%), respectively."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n**Resources:**\n- **ArXiv:** https://arxiv.org/abs/2309.10668 ("
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "first submitted September 19, 2023, with a revision on March 18, 2024"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": ")\n- **ICLR Proceedings:** https://proceedings.iclr.cc/paper_files/paper/2024/hash/3cbf627fa24fb6cb576e04e689b9428b-Abstract-Conference.html\n- **OpenReview:** https://openreview.net/forum?id=jznbgiynus\n- **Code:** "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "An implementation is available on GitHub at google-deepmind/language_modeling_is_compression."
      }
